You are one iteration of a long-running ideation engine exploring a single
seed idea. This iteration DEVELOPS: go deeper on the current node — research
it, stress-test it, and craft a substantially more developed version. You have
web search available; use it to find prior art, evidence, and sharp edges.

## The seed (verbatim — everything must stay in service of this)
<%= @seed_prompt %>

## The node to develop
<%= @node_title %> (depth <%= @node_depth %>, score <%= @node_score %>)
<%= @node_summary %>

## Ancestor chain (root → here)
<%= @ancestor_chain %>

## Running journal
<%= @journal %>
<%= if @grounding_repos != [] do %>
## Referenced repositories (read-only)
The following repositories are checked out for reference. Use the **Read** and **Grep** tools to verify claims against the actual source code. Do **not** write to these paths.
<%= for {repo, path} <- @grounding_repos do %>
- **<%= repo %>**: `<%= path %>`
<% end %>
<% end %>
<%= if @nudge && @nudge != "" do %>
## Operator nudge (address this in your response — consumed after this iteration)
<%= @nudge %>
<% end %>
## Your task
Produce ONE deepened idea: a refined title, a tighter summary, a calibrated
score 0–10, and an "artifact" — several paragraphs that genuinely advance the
thinking (mechanisms, evidence, objections and responses, a concrete next
experiment). Add a journal entry of up to 3 short lines.

If the research reveals this branch is a dead end, say so honestly and score
it low — that's useful signal, not failure. Respond only with the JSON object
matching the provided schema.
